                    referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise-info">
                <h2>Deep Breathing</h2>
                <p>A fundamental technique to calm your nervous system. Focus on slow, deep inhales and exhales.</p>
                <p><strong>Instructions:</strong> Find a comfortable position. Inhale deeply through your nose, filling
                    your abdomen. Exhale slowly through your mouth. Repeat for 5-10 minutes.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="exercise-card">
            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/EvMTrP8eRvM?si=mPpOUfMSkkltttaW"
                    title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0"
                    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                    referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise-info">
                <h2>Gentle Stretching</h2>
                <p>Releasing physical tension can significantly reduce mental stress. Focus on slow, mindful movements.
                </p>
                <p><strong>Instructions:</strong> Gently stretch your neck, shoulders, arms, and legs. Hold each stretch
                    for 20-30 seconds. Avoid any painful movements.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="exercise-card">
            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/MIr3RsUWrdo?si=L5FgylFXk8w-1U6L"
                    title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0"
                    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                    referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise-info">
                <h2>Mindful Meditation</h2>
                <p>Bringing your awareness to the present moment without judgment can help quiet the mind and reduce
                    stress.</p>
                <p><strong>Instructions:</strong> Find a quiet place. Sit or lie down comfortably. Focus on your breath,
                    bodily sensations, or sounds around you. Gently redirect your attention when your mind wanders.</p>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="exercise-card">
            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_1h-zizAGsc?si=FfVadbmqejKhGSod"
                    title="YouTube video player" frameborder="0"
                    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                    referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <div class="exercise-info">
                <h2>Progressive Muscle Relaxation</h2>
                <p>A technique involving tensing and then releasing different muscle groups in the body to promote
                    relaxation.</p>
                <p><strong>Instructions:</strong> Start with your toes, tense them tightly for a few seconds, then
                    release completely. Move up through your body, tensing and releasing each muscle group (calves,
                    thighs, glutes, abdomen, chest, arms, hands, face).</p>
            </div>
        </section>
